<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddb48d48e-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s541"><num value="541">§ 541.</num><heading> Tax on circulating notes generally</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In lieu of all existing taxes, every association shall pay to the Treasurer of the United States, in the months of January and July, a duty of one-half of 1 per centum each half year upon the average amount of its notes in circulation.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddb48d48f-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(R.S. § 5214; <ref href="/us/act/1883-03-03/ch121/s1">Mar. 3, 1883, ch. 121, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/22/488">22 Stat. 488</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="iddb48d490-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="iddb48d491-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="iddb48d492-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">R.S. § 5214 derived from <ref href="/us/act/1864-06-03/ch106/s41">act June 3, 1864, ch. 106, § 41</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/13/111">13 Stat. 111</ref>, which was part of the National Bank Act. See <ref href="/us/usc/t12/s38">section 38 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
